# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have to flip the bits, i.e. we have to find compliment, thus I think ~n is a really good option, but we have a problem over here, it flips all the bits  that is if an integer only takes 7 bits and rest in front are zeros, it will flip them too which is not required! Thus let's find the number of bits in which a number can fit in, suppose we have 20 only, it's binary representation is 10100 and  by this formula: 

##### nBits = (Math.log(num) / Math.log(2)) + 1

We can get the number of bits in which our number will definitely fit in, thus now let's prevent our prefix zeros to flip, thus create a mask 

##### mask = (1 << nBits) - 1;

This will make sure all prefix zeros are preserved, thus let's save our zeros now! I hope & will work as it will make 1-0 = 0 and 1-1 = 0, thus & our ~num with our mask

##### ans = ~num & mask

HERE WE GO! LINEAR TIME AND SPACE!

