Learning points:
1. xor with one is used to toggle the bits.
2. All bits of  2^n -1 will be set i.e. one. 
```
class Solution {
public:
    int numberOfDigit(int num){
        int cnt =0;
        while(num){
            cnt++;
            num/=2;
        } 
        return cnt;
    }
    int findComplement(int num) {
        int n = numberOfDigit(num);
        long long int x = pow(2,n);// long long int is taken to avoid overflow
        x--;
        return num^x;
    }
};
```

Caution point: negation will not work because it will toggle the left zero bits to one. Since the input is signed int, so negation operation will also change the the number into negative.

