Lets take a example. Num is 10 => 0b1010
we now need to invert the 1s to 0s
actually , the number is stored as "0b0000000......0001010" in unint32_t.
if we directly invert the number , we will also shift the preceeding 0s to 1s.
we can flip only the bits in our number if we have some kind of mask that is '0b0000000000...0001111'
to get the mask , we can calculate the MSB position as floor(log2(num)) . here , msb position is 4 
then,to create the mask , we do left shift opertation on "0b1111111111...1111" to get "0b0000000...1111"

now we invert the original Number and then perform And operation with the mask to set the preceeding 1s to 0
0b0000000....1111 & 0b111111....0101 = 0b00000000......0101



```
class Solution {
public:
    int bitwiseComplement(uint32_t N) {
        if(N==0)
            return 1;
        uint32_t msbPos = log2(N); //get msb 1 position 
        uint32_t mask = INT_MAX>>(31-msbPos); //get 1s mask on the required number
        uint32_t invert = ~N;  //Flip all the bits in original number
        return invert&mask;  //set the preceeding 1s to 0s using mask

    }
};
```

