solutions.content:
You can basically use logical negation operator `~` to invert bits, the only challenge is to mask the bits that you want, here's a solution:
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findComplement(int num) {
		// 1) Find number of bits in input
         int bitCount = log2(abs(num)) + 1;

		 // 2) Create a mask that should be all 1s
		 // e.g. if bitCount is 3, we want it to be 111 (aka 7 in decimal)
		 // to create mask you can left shift bits by bits count then subtract 1
		 // only issue is it will cause signed integer overflow if bit count is 31 becuase it will be INT_MIN - 1
		 // so we account for this case
         if(bitCount == 31) return INT_MAX - num;

		 // create the mask as descriped above
         int mask = (1 << bitCount) - 1;

		 // 3) Negate number and apply mask
         return (~num) & mask;
    }
};
```

