**CONCEPT TO REMEMBER: The Hamming distance between two integers is the number of positions at which the corresponding bits are different.**
So to calculate the difference (distance ), we must check if at a specific position the the bit of 2 numbers are different or same, if same then the difference is 0, else 1 , just like xor operation(gives 1 when bits are different else gives 0).
1.count no. of 1's , subtract no. of 1's from total length of the array, which gives total no. of integers with 0 at that position,i.e., count of 0's at that specific position.
2.multiply count of 0's and count of 1's at specific postion, to get hamming distance of that particular position.
3.now repeat the above 2 steps and sum all of the hamming distances, to obtain total hamming distance 
```
class Solution {
    public int totalHammingDistance(int[] nums) {
         int result = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i<32; i++){
              int count_ones= 0;
            for(int j = 0; j<nums.length; j++){
                count_ones+=(nums[j]>>i)&1; //count no. of 1's at a specific position
            }
            result +=(count_ones*(nums.length-count_ones));
        }
        return result;  
    }
}
```

