# Intutions
Basic intution says, **what if I get the count of opposite bits on the curr index** then I will add all for 32 bits and get the result

that's what I just coded here;

if 1 then look into how many zeros are present on that index
if 0 then look into how many one are present on that index

Also it will be helpful if I remove curr_bit as it is not going to play a role to ans;
```

class Solution {
public:
    int totalHammingDistance(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        int zeroCnt[32];
        int oneCnt[32];
        memset(zeroCnt, 0, sizeof(zeroCnt));
        memset(oneCnt, 0, sizeof(oneCnt));

        //counting the total zero and one in bit of number; eg,. 5-> 101 , one:2, zero:1
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<32;j++){
                if((nums[i] & (1<<j)) ==0 ){
                    zeroCnt[j]++;
                } else oneCnt[j]++;
            }
        }

        //if 0 then look into how many 1 we currently have also remove the curr bit ie 0 from the zeroCnt;
 \xA0 \xA0 \xA0 \xA0//if 1 then look into how many 0 we currently have also remove the curr bit ie 1 from the onCnt;

        int ans=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<32;j++){
                if((nums[i] & (1<<j))==0) { //look in oneCnt;
                    ans+= oneCnt[j];
                    zeroCnt[j]--;
                } else{ //look in zeroCnt;
                    ans+= zeroCnt[j];
                    oneCnt[j]--;
                }
            }
        }

        //TC-> O(32*N)=O(N),  32 bits and n diff number
        //SC-> O(32+32)=O(1), using only 32+32 extra space;
        return ans;
    }
};
```

